primary.context: Caller has never logged in before and needs a registration link
primary.detail: The agent verified the caller and sent a Clubhouse registration link to the updated email address.

steps: Agent identified the caller's need for account access.
Agent performed account lookup and identity verification.
Agent identified that the contact information on file was incorrect.
Agent updated the email and phone number for the delivery of the link.
Agent sent the Clubhouse registration link and confirmed completion.

clarifications.note: Agent confirming if registration link is needed
Agent re-verifying phone after initial mismatch

corrections.note: Caller corrected email and phone number on file

actions.detail: Sent registration link to updated Gmail address

insights.summary: The caller wanted to set up their owner's account for the first time. The agent successfully verified the caller, corrected their contact information, and sent a Clubhouse registration link.
